<div dir="ltr"><span class="" id=":1kk.1" tabindex="-1">OSHMEM</span> <span class="" id=":1kk.2" tabindex="-1">memheap</span> implementation relies on the Â &quot;_end&quot; symbol provided by <span class="" id=":1kk.3" tabindex="-1">linux</span> linker. The _end symbol indicates the beginning of the program dynamic allocation area.<div>
This is needed to allow programmatic access to the process global/static variables.<br><div><br></div></div><div><br></div></div><div class="gmail_extra"><br><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Thu, Jul 24, 2014 at 9:22 PM, Marco Atzeri <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:marco.atzeri@gmail.com" target="_blank">marco.atzeri@gmail.com</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br>
